overview: The user wanted to significantly improve the aesthetic appeal of their
  sleep questionnaire application, which they felt was functional but lacked a
  refined style. The agent initiated a thorough review of the app's current
  visual design, including its color palette, typography, spacing, form
  elements, and overall visual interest. Based on this analysis, the agent
  identified key areas for improvement, such as introducing a more
  sophisticated, sleep-themed color palette, enhancing typography, adding visual
  elements for delight, and refining form component styling. The implementation
  involved updating the global CSS with new sleep-themed colors, redesigning the
  main questionnaire form layout, improving the progress bar, enhancing the
  introductory section with better visual hierarchy, and polishing individual UI
  components like checkboxes, radio buttons, and sliders. The goal was to
  transform the app's visual language to evoke a sense of calm and
  professionalism, tailored for a sleep assessment experience.
